senses.sense_definition: A tree of the species Casuarina equisetifolia, resembling a pine tree, native to Southeast Asia and Australia.

examples.text: The <w>agoho</w> tree is often mistaken for a pine due to its needle-like foliage.
Local authorities planted an <w>agoho</w> forest along the coast to prevent soil erosion.

senses.sense_definition: A specific barangay located in the municipality of Calauag in the Philippines.

examples.text: My friend traveled to <w>Agoho</w> to visit his relatives during the holidays.
The community center in <w>Agoho</w> hosted a festival for the local residents.
